There are different AWS technology layers 
The stack starts with 1. ML frameworks 
                      2. AI / ML services 
                      3. Generative AI

ML frameworks layers
 Core : Amazon sagemaker : a fully managed machine learning service that you can use to build, train, and deploy your own custom models. 
                           SageMaker provides tools and infrastructure to accelerate your ML development and deployment lifecycle.

AI / ML services :   text and documents domain - Amazon Comprehend for natural language processing
                      Amazon Translate  - language translation
                      Amazon Textract -  extracting data from scanned documents.

                     chatbots 
                       Amazon Lex - use to build conversational interfaces powered by the same deep learning technologies that drive Amazon Alexa

                     speech domain  
                       Amazon polly - text -to-speech 
                       Amazon transcribe - automatic speech recognition

                    vision domain
                      Amazon rekognition - DL computer vision service that can analyze images and videos for a wide range of applications.

                    for Search 
                      Amazon kendra - reimagines enterprise search for websites and applications.

                    recommendations domain
                      Amazon personalize - real time personalization and recommendations.

                    misc 
                     AWS DeepRacer - fully autonomous 1/18th scale race car that lets you get hands- on experiecne with RL


Generative AI
   Amazon Bedrock : fully managed servcie that can make FMs from Amazon and leading AI startups available through an API
   Amazon Q -  a gen AI powered assistant designed to work that can be tailored for a business's data.
